 26/05/Phenology-1280-x-720.png
UID:9rP9BYsjaUCAOj9-zcMwp
SUMMARY:Fourth Saturday Phenology Walk
DTSTAMP:20260617T163156Z
DTSTART:20260627T090000Z
DESCRIPTION:Fourth Saturday of the Month9:00 – 11:00 amFree\, donations app
	reciatedAll ages\, minors must be accompanied by an adult \n\n\n\nMeet in 
	front of the Nature Center building \n\n\n\nDiscover the hidden seasonal r
	hythms of nature firsthand on our guided Phenology Walks\, where we track 
	the life cycles of different plants across ecosystems\, from the first spr
	ing bud burst to winter dormancy. You’ll learn how shifting weather patter
	ns and climate change influence the timing of these important events in ou
	r local ecosystems and how you can become a community scientist\, contribu
	ting vital data from your own backyard to a global research initiative.  \
	n\n\n\nThese relaxing morning walks are led by scientists from Rice Univer
	sity and staff from the Arboretum. We welcome nature enthusiasts of all ag
	es\, however kids 12 years and younger must be accompanied by a guardian. 
	\n\n\n\nLearn more about the study of phenology and ways you can contribut
	e at https://www.usanpn.org/nn \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCommunity Science Partner\n
	\nhttps://houstonarboretum.org/event/fourth-saturday-phenology-walk/2026-0
	6-27/\n\nFrom Houston Arboretum & Nature Center
URL:https://houstonarboretum.org/event/fourth-saturday-phenology-walk/2026-
	06-27/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:houston-arboretum
CATEGORIES:Houston Arboretum & Nature Center
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
